I would like to extend the domain of the following function: $$	ext{Li}_0^{(1,0)}(z):=-\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\ln(n)z^{n}\qquad	ext{where }|z|<1$$ The part in red is the series, the part in green is a hypothetical extension I'll start by saying that I don't know any techniques for doing something like this, so any advice (links, names of theorems or similar) is useful. I could only find the value in $x=-1$ $$	ext{Li}_0^{(1,0)}(-1)=\lim_{s	o 0}\left[ \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}  rac{(-1)^n\ln(n)}{n^s}ight] = - rac{1}{2}\ln\left( rac{\pi}{2}ight)$$ I've searched for possible representations on Wolfram , but none include the one with $
u=0$ Unfortunately I found the integral representation of polylogarithms $	ext{Li}_{
u}(z)$ only for $\Re(
