u}(z) =  rac{i}{2 π} \int_{-i ∞ + γ}^{i ∞ + γ} (-t)^{1 - 
u}\ln(-t) (-z)^{-t} Γ(-t) Γ(t) \mathrm{d}t$$ $$	ext{Li}^{(1,0)}_{0}(z) = - rac{i}{2 π} \int_{-i ∞ + γ}^{i ∞ + γ} \ln(-t) (-z)^{-t} Γ(-t) Γ(t+1) \mathrm{d}t$$ $$	ext{Li}^{(1,0)}_{0}(z) =  rac{i}{2} \int_{-i ∞ + γ}^{i ∞ + γ} \ln(-t) (-z)^{-t} \csc(\pi t) \mathrm{d}t$$ But with this function I would also like to work with graphs and I don't use programs that know how to manage this type of representations with complex numbers. Would anyone be able to suggest an alternative method to represent it? Update 1 The graph is something like this: Update 2 I obtained the following property: $$\Re\left[	ext{Li}_0^{(1,0)}\left(e^{2\pi i x}ight)ight]=- rac{1}{2}\left(\gamma+\ln\left(2\piight)+ rac{\psi\left(xight)+\psi\left(1-xight)}{2}ight)\qquad	ext{for } 0<x<1$$ Hence also the following formulas for $n\geq 1$ : $$ egin{align}\Re\left[	ext{Li}_{-2n}^{(1,0)}\left(e^{2\pi i x}ight)ight]&=& rac{(-1)^{n-1}}{(2\pi)^{2n}} rac{\psi^{(2n)}\left(xight)+\psi^{(2n)}\left(1-xight)}{4}\\Im\left[	ext{Li}_{-(2n-1)}^{(1,0)}\left(e^{2\pi i x}ight)ight]&=& rac{(-1)^{n-1}}{(2\pi)^{2n-1}} rac{\psi^{(2n-1)}\left(xight)-\psi^{(2n-1)}\left(1-xight)}{4}\end{align}$$

